HEADWORD: Cœrulignone
<hw>C⟦oe⟧`ru*lig"none</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coeruleus cerulean + lignum</ets> wood + E.
quin<ets>one</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bluish violet,
crystalline substance obtained in the purification of crude wood
vinegar. It is regarded as a complex quinone derivative of diphenyl; --
called also <altname>cedriret</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coessential</ent>⟦br⟧
